1. Flexbox
Make Container Flexible
.container{
    display: flex;
}
2. Main Axis Alignment
justify-content: center;

Options:

justify-content: flex-start;
justify-content: center;
justify-content: flex-end;
justify-content: space-between;
justify-content: space-around;
space-between
Logo              Links

Used in your navbar.

3. Cross Axis Alignment
align-items: center;

Aligns items vertically.

4. Flex Direction
Row (Default)
flex-direction: row;
A B C
Column
flex-direction: column;
A
B
C

Used in the login form.

5. Gap
gap: 20px;

Adds spacing between flex items.

Used in:

Navbar links
Gallery items
6. Flex Wrap
flex-wrap: wrap;

Moves items to the next row when space runs out.

nowrap (Default)
flex-wrap: nowrap;

All items stay in one row.

wrap
flex-wrap: wrap;
1 2 3 4
5 6 7 8

Used in Photo Gallery.

7. Centering a Login Form
main{
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    height: 100vh;
}
100vh

Means full screen height.

8. Box Shadow
box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);

Adds depth to elements.

Used in Login Form.

9. Border Radius
border-radius: 10px;

Rounds corners.

10. Hover Effect
Transition
transition: 0.3s ease;

Makes animation smooth.

Scale
transform: scale(1.05);

Enlarges element on hover.

Example:

img:hover{
    transform: scale(1.05);
}
11. Object Fit
object-fit: cover;

Prevents image distortion.

Used in Gallery.

12. Media Queries

Used to make websites responsive.

@media (max-width: 768px){
    footer{
        flex-direction: column;
    }
}
